Want to fill out your Epic game army with more human soldiers?

Maybe time to print some Colonial/Napoleonic praetorian looking units for your 6mm sci-fi wars.

Would fit in nice with any imperial guard or similar leaning army.

Here are a select bunch of models Pre-supported and ready to print.

Soldiers are about 6 mm from eyes to disc and total 7mm tall without the disc they are standing on.

Disc is 1mm thick and 5mm in diameter



Please note that when printed at this scale much of the details will be lost compared to the computer renderings.
See printed pictures printed at 0.03mm

New poses added for your favourite cannon fodder, now you can make them parade in front of the enemy so they can improve their shooting skills!
Also, apparently the grunts are wasting too much ammo, so here are some reloading poses.

As always, included supported and unsupported versions for each model, you can find one .rar for each group (rifle up, reloading and parading).
Thingivers force to upload at least one STL file, so that guy is just a random pose from the bunch.
